org.ndnx.ndn.profiles.security.access.group
Class NodeKey

java.lang.Object
  org.ndnx.ndn.profiles.security.access.group.NodeKey

public class NodeKey
extends Object

This class represents node keys. It includes methods for computing derived node keys for descendant nodes using a key derivation function. For a definition and description of node keys, see the NDNx Access Control Specification.

Field Detail

DEFAULT_NODE_KEY_LENGTH

public static final int DEFAULT_NODE_KEY_LENGTH
Default data key length in bytes. No real reason this can't be bumped up to 32. It acts as the seed for a KDF, not an encryption key.

See Also:
Constant Field Values

DEFAULT_NODE_KEY_ALGORITHM

public static final String DEFAULT_NODE_KEY_ALGORITHM
The keys we're wrapping are really seeds for a KDF, not keys in their own right. Eventually we'll use CMAC, so call them AES...
